message: Start by combining two raw ingredients, then use the stove once on the resulting mixture to cook it. This usually gets you to 40-60 value. You can sometimes add a third raw ingredient (like a vegetable) to reach 60. The highest values (around 80) were achieved by combining a cooked two-ingredient dish with a raw grain like bread. Be careful not to add too many ingredients (4+) or cook an already complex item multiple times, as this often leads to 'overcomplicated' or 'overcooked' items with zero or negative value. The water tool usually decreases value.

message: Always cook raw proteins and vegetables with the stove first to increase their base value to 20. The most valuable combinations involve 2 or 3 ingredients. To reach 60, combine a cooked protein and a cooked vegetable. To reach 80, combine that 60-value item with a grain. Crucially, *do not combine four or more ingredients*, as this consistently results in 'overcomplicated' items with zero or negative value. The 'water' tool seemed to degrade items in my playthrough, so use it with extreme caution.
